==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*delban''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[delva]], Old Saxon bi[[delban]] (Dutch [[delven]]), Old High German bi[[telban]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'delvan/

===Verb===
'''delfan''' (class III strong)
# to [[dig]]
#:''Ongan he eorþan delfan'': he began to dig the earth.  (''Codex Vercellensis'')
# to dig up, to [[excavate]]

